data.description: It wasn't long ago that those of us shopping for a car would pull up to empty dealership lots with hardly an option in sight. Beggars can't be choosers, but there are few of us willing to drive away in a lavender, base-model Honda minivan. The larger the purchase, the more we're driven to hold out for something better. Something that feels like a reward. A step up. A prize. Something like 102 Kaladar Court, a gift to buyers who've refused to settle. You feel the sellers' care and pride of ownership from the curb, evidenced by sparkling new paint (outside and in), beautiful landscaping, tasteful lighting, and new quartz kitchen countertops, just to name a few. Those needing a second living space or office will cherish the vaulted study tucked in front of the family room. The green, shady backyard is entrancing, like staring at a waterfall or the night sky. It filters just the right amount of sunlight to create a natural, retreat-like experience inside. As part of the perennially popular Oxxford Hunt neighborhood that adjoins Bond Lake and Park, there's so much to do outdoors, from walking trails to swimming and tennis. Rather than settling for any old home, settle into a great one. ©
